{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#3173: :class=\"undefined\" causes class being rendered",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:28:01.460121+00:00",
  "text": ":class=\"undefined\" causes class being rendered\n\n### Version\r\n\r\n3.2.6\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<template>\r\n  <div :title=\"undefined\" :class=\"undefined\" :style=\"undefined\">\r\n    Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Dolore molestiae quod voluptas\r\n    reprehenderit possimus nihil eligendi iure et esse aut, iste natus porro enim rerum cumque\r\n    veniam quae! Quam, voluptatum.\r\n  </div>\r\n</template>\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\nNone of `title`, `class`, `style` should be rendered.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\n`class` is rendered, the same thing applies to `null`.\r\n\r\n### Additional info\r\n\r\nThis was fixed in v3.1.5 but is [reproducible](https://sfc.vuejs.org/#eyJBcHAudnVlIjoiPHRlbXBsYXRlPlxuICA8ZGl2IDp0aXRsZT1cInVuZGVmaW5lZFwiIDpjbGFzcz1cInVuZGVmaW5lZFwiIDpzdHlsZT1cInVuZGVmaW5lZFwiPlxuICAgIGZvb1xuICA8L2Rpdj5cbjwvdGVtcGxhdGU+In0=) when using the latest commit.\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
